# CI until green (default)

Unless the user explicitly opts out (e.g. "don't wait for CI", "status only", "stop fixing CI"), **always drive CI to green** after making or pushing changes.

## Default loop

1. Run fast local checks: `./scripts/ci-validate.sh`
2. Push if there are unpushed commits
3. Check PR / Kind smoke status: `./scripts/from-here.sh status` or `fix-ci`
4. On failure: read `gh run view <id> --log-failed`, patch root cause, push, repeat
5. When green: report success; merge only if user asked to merge

## Opt-out phrases (do not fix loop)

- "status only" / "just status"
- "don't wait for CI" / "skip CI"
- "stop fixing" / "don't merge"

## Do not

- Poll Kind smoke for 90 minutes in one blocking turn without reporting progress
- Open Codespaces for CI failures (Option B first; Option A only after green if user wants hands-on)
- Pin versions to make CI pass — fix config per `dependencies.mdc`

## Commands

```bash
./scripts/from-here.sh check local
./scripts/from-here.sh fix-ci
./scripts/from-here.sh monitor    # when user wants to wait for completion
```

See `docs/cloud-agent.md`.
